               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18381231-name-200" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18381231-name-200" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18381231-name-200" type="surname" value="HARVEY"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18381231-name-200" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>WILLIAM HARVEY</persName>
                  </hi>. I live in Wellington-street, Chelsea, and am an omnibus driver. On the 19th of December, at a quarter before ten o'clock</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="183812310022"></xptr>
               <p>in the evening, I placed my whip on the foot board of the omnibus—I was then near the Man in the Moon public-house, in King's-road, Chelsea—I got down, and I returned in two or three minutes—my whip was them gone—this is it—(<hi rend="italic">looking at it.</hi>)</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18381231-name-201" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18381231-name-201" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18381231-name-201" type="surname" value="PHILLIPS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18381231-name-201" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>JOHN PHILLIPS</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">police-constable T</hi> 139.) I was on duty on the night in question about half a mile from the Man in the Moon—I met the prisoner with this whip—I stopped and asked where he got it—he said he had had it in his possession for twelve months, and he had been All omnibus driver for Mr. Butcher—I looked at the thong, and it appeared to have been used that day—I said if he could take me to any place to satisfy me I would go with him; if not I must take him to the station-house—he could not, and I took him—he then said he had found it.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner's Defence.</hi> I found it in the Fulham-road—I did not say I had had it twelve months.</p>
